sequenceDiagram
    participant User as 👤 User
    participant Booker as Booker Form
    participant Handler as handleNewBooking
    participant SpamCheck as SpamCheckService<br/>(NEW)
    participant CombinedSvc as CombinedBlockingService<br/>(NEW)
    participant GlobalDB as Global Watchlist DB
    participant OrgDB as Org Watchlist DB
    participant AuditSvc as AuditService
    participant Router as Router
    participant FakePage as /booking-successful<br/>(NEW)

    User->>Booker: Submit booking form
    Booker->>Handler: Create booking request
    
    Note over Handler: Email validation
    
    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Handler,SpamCheck: NEW: Spam check initialization
        Handler->>SpamCheck: startCheck(email, orgId)
        SpamCheck->>CombinedSvc: isBlocked(email, orgId)
    end
    
    Note over Handler,CombinedSvc: ⚡ Spam check runs in PARALLEL<br/>with availability loading (zero delay)
    
    par Parallel Execution
        rect rgb(255, 250, 205)
            Note over CombinedSvc,OrgDB: Check Global + Org Level Blocking
            CombinedSvc->>GlobalDB: Check global email
            GlobalDB-->>CombinedSvc: Result
            CombinedSvc->>GlobalDB: Check global domain
            GlobalDB-->>CombinedSvc: Result
            alt If orgId provided
                CombinedSvc->>OrgDB: Check org email
                OrgDB-->>CombinedSvc: Result
                CombinedSvc->>OrgDB: Check org domain
                OrgDB-->>CombinedSvc: Result
            end
            alt If blocked found
                CombinedSvc->>AuditSvc: Log blocked attempt
            end
        end
        CombinedSvc-->>SpamCheck: Promise<BlockingResult>
    and
        Handler->>Handler: Load availability
        Handler->>Handler: Process event type
        Handler->>Handler: Check booking limits
    end
    
    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Handler,SpamCheck: NEW: Wait for spam check result
        Handler->>SpamCheck: waitForCheck()
        SpamCheck-->>Handler: BlockingResult<br/>(checked both global & org)
    end
    
    alt Email is Blocked (Spammer Path)
        rect rgb(255, 200, 200)
            Note over Handler: NEW: Generate fake booking in handleNewBooking
            Handler->>Handler: Generate decoy response<br/>- Fake UUID<br/>- isSpamDecoy: true<br/>- All required fields<br/>- No DB write
            Handler-->>Booker: Fake booking data
            Note over Booker: NEW: Detect isSpamDecoy flag
            Booker->>Router: Redirect with query params
            Router->>FakePage: Show fake success page
            Note over FakePage: Spammer sees<br/>convincing confirmation<br/>(Blocked by global OR org watchlist)
        end
    else Email is Clean (Legitimate Path)
        rect rgb(200, 255, 200)
            Handler->>GlobalDB: Create real booking
            GlobalDB-->>Handler: Booking created
            Handler-->>Booker: Real booking data
            Booker->>Router: Normal booking flow
            Router->>Router: Standard success page
        end
    end
    
    Note over Handler,FakePage: Architecture:<br/>✅ SpamCheckService.ts (NEW) - Async wrapper with startCheck/waitForCheck<br/>✅ CombinedBlockingService.ts (NEW) - Checks global + org blocking with audit logging<br/>✅ GlobalBlockingService.ts (MODIFIED) - Now takes orgRepo instead of auditService, checks global + org domains<br/>✅ OrganizationBlockingService.ts (MODIFIED) - Optional audit logging<br/>✅ spamCheck.ts container (NEW) - DI container for spam check<br/>✅ /booking-successful/page.tsx (NEW) - Fake success page<br/>📝 handleNewBooking.ts (MODIFIED) - Async spam check + fake booking<br/>📝 useBookings.ts (MODIFIED) - Redirect logic for isSpamDecoy<br/>📝 bookings/types.ts (MODIFIED) - Added isSpamDecoy flag
